      "side": 1,
      "message": "The problem is not that unknown fields cause the code to break. The problem is that unknown fields are not round-tripped by the old code. It reads the cacheEntry, modifies it, stores it back. All fields it doesn\u0027t know about are lost. So when new code adds \"id_token\" field, old binaries will actively keep erasing it.\n\nUsing protobuf naively won\u0027t solve this problem. I have never tried working with unrecognized fields in protobufs, I\u0027ll see how hard it is. Perhaps it\u0027s not very hard.",
      "parentUuid": "51cc9c01_55e94494",
      "revId": "9f9db5542890cb5291bb8b61dc3ef8c2ce954bfd",
